      "id": "PopularPost296655",
      "post_content": "Kryptnyt, you miss the point. Against a blue, black, or blue/black deck (where the creatures are more focused on their abilities than being durable), reliably getting new creatures can be a big advantage. Not to mention that this is one spell to sneak through all those counterspells that can yield a lot of power down the road.Especially with [Overrun](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Overrun) effects.  \n  \nThat said, 3.9 may be a bit high of a rating, as it is right now...  \n  \n3/5",
